    <edge source="&quot;TENANT&quot;" target="&quot;LANDLORD&quot;">
      <data key="d3">127.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Landlord and Tenant have a legal relationship wherein the Tenant agrees to pay rent in exchange for the right to occupy the Landlord's property."&lt;SEP&gt;"Landlords and tenants are parties to a rental agreement, each having specified rights and responsibilities as defined by the Residential Landlord and Tenant Ordinance."&lt;SEP&gt;"Landlords have a contractual relationship with tenants, providing rental properties in exchange for payment and adhering to legal obligations."."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Landlord and Tenant have a contractual relationship defined by the rental agreement that outlines mutual obligations and rights."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Tenant and Landlord are in a contractual relationship defined by the Rental Agreement, with specific rights and responsibilities for both parties."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Tenant has a contractual relationship with the Landlord, requiring the Landlord to fulfill certain obligations and maintain the property for the Tenant's use."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Tenant interacts with the Landlord regarding rental payments and the management of security deposits."&lt;SEP&gt;"The landlord and tenant enter into a rental agreement which stipulates the rights and responsibilities of both parties during the tenancy."&lt;SEP&gt;"The landlord and tenant have a contractual relationship established through the rental agreement, which outlines their rights and obligations."|&lt;|"contractual relationship, rights and obligations"&lt;SEP&gt;"The landlord and tenant have a contractual relationship governed by the rental agreement, which outlines their rights and responsibilities."&lt;SEP&gt;"The landlord and tenant relationship is defined by rental agreements that stipulate rights, obligations, and remedies for both parties."&lt;SEP&gt;"The landlord is responsible for managing the property rented to the tenant and maintaining the terms of their rental agreement."&lt;SEP&gt;"The relationship between landlord and tenant is foundational in rental agreements, with the landlord providing the dwelling unit and the tenant agreeing to occupancy terms."&lt;SEP&gt;"The tenant has a contractual relationship with the landlord as they rent the property, requiring both parties to adhere to the terms of the rental agreement."</data>
      <data key="d5">"contractual relationship, housing"&lt;SEP&gt;"contractual relationship, obligations"&lt;SEP&gt;"contractual relationship, rights and obligations"&lt;SEP&gt;"contractual relationship, rights and responsibilities"&lt;SEP&gt;"contractual relationship, tenant rights"&lt;SEP&gt;"contractual relationship, tenant-landlord dynamics"&lt;SEP&gt;"parties to agreement, mutual obligations"&lt;SEP&gt;"rental agreement, legal obligations"&lt;SEP&gt;"rental relationship, legal obligations"&lt;SEP&gt;"rental relationship, occupancy"&lt;SEP&gt;"rental relationship, property management"&lt;SEP&gt;9</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-c3bc1dbbc22da4bbc6a6de45ffaa66df&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b6545ef03dc8e11cfc621983d50e00f5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8afa5a33f6f01f872089d10f74700726&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-948f888104b901aa818d8a64425e31e7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7759df7263a7c6a25e1e83bd43ddc9c9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-caa542bbeffaceb300226b5da0f70961&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1b28d02fb2d5d40898b1812c5ffa049c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-49eeebcde41c80ab078e5fdc2db008fa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9177bd0c8a93a10bd432b21c5f8d990c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-471bca0f3da3db4a8af4c1624c74f5ad&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bc145ddced779a4e72a5f21656d00d2e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bbf2a304267f411fdd75632601e64887&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b822667a3deb6498c36004d88d76787b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d2157989b5839c3e9aeb71adca8d9db4</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;TENANT&quot;" target="&quot;DWELLING UNIT&quot;">
      <data key="d3">38.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"A tenant occupies a dwelling unit based on the rental agreement made with the landlord, establishing their residential relationship."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Tenant has the right to occupy the Dwelling Unit as per the rental agreement, which stipulates their residential rights."&lt;SEP&gt;"The tenant occupies the dwelling unit as per the terms outlined in the rental agreement, which defines their living arrangement and rights."&lt;SEP&gt;"The tenant occupies the dwelling unit under the terms of the rental agreement, establishing a direct connection to the space."|&lt;|"occupancy, contractual relationship"</data>
      <data key="d5">"housing, rental agreement"&lt;SEP&gt;"occupational rights, tenancy"&lt;SEP&gt;"residency, occupancy"&lt;SEP&gt;10</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-b6545ef03dc8e11cfc621983d50e00f5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bbf2a304267f411fdd75632601e64887&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7759df7263a7c6a25e1e83bd43ddc9c9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d2157989b5839c3e9aeb71adca8d9db4</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;TENANT&quot;" target="&quot;PERIODIC TENANCY&quot;">
      <data key="d3">8.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"A periodic tenancy outlines the duration and conditions under which tenants may inhabit a dwelling unit until terminated."</data>
      <data key="d5">"tenancy structure, occupancy duration"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-d2157989b5839c3e9aeb71adca8d9db4</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;TENANT&quot;" target="&quot;REPAIRS&quot;">
      <data key="d3">8.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The tenant may request repairs from the landlord as part of their right to a well-maintained living environment."</data>
      <data key="d5">"maintenance request, tenant rights"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-caa542bbeffaceb300226b5da0f70961</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;TENANT&quot;" target="&quot;INJUNCTIVE RELIEF&quot;">
      <data key="d3">17.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Tenants may seek injunctive relief if the landlord conducts unlawful entry or harassment."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Tenant may seek Injunctive Relief to compel the Landlord to fulfill their obligations under the rental agreement."</data>
      <data key="d5">"legal action, tenant protection"&lt;SEP&gt;"legal remedy, compliance"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-bbf2a304267f411fdd75632601e64887&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-caa542bbeffaceb300226b5da0f70961</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;TENANT&quot;" target="&quot;SECURITY DEPOSIT&quot;">
      <data key="d3">9.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The tenant pays a security deposit to the landlord as part of securing the rental agreement and protecting potential damages or unpaid rent."</data>
      <data key="d5">"financial obligation, rental agreement"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-7759df7263a7c6a25e1e83bd43ddc9c9</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;TENANT&quot;" target="&quot;EXCESS INTEREST&quot;">
      <data key="d3">7.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The tenant is entitled to receive any excess interest accrued from their security deposit that is held longer than six months, as stipulated in the rental agreement."</data>
      <data key="d5">"financial rights, rental agreement"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-7759df7263a7c6a25e1e83bd43ddc9c9</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;TENANT&quot;" target="&quot;CITY COMPTROLLER&quot;">
      <data key="d3">8.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The City Comptroller provides essential information regarding interest rates on security deposits that affect tenants."</data>
      <data key="d5">"financial regulation, tenant information"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-bc145ddced779a4e72a5f21656d00d2e</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;TENANT&quot;" target="&quot;TRANSFEROR&quot;">
      <data key="d3">8.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Transferor remains jointly liable to the Tenant for the security deposit until a formal transfer occurs."</data>
      <data key="d5">"liability, rental agreement"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-bc145ddced779a4e72a5f21656d00d2e</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;TENANT&quot;" target="&quot;DAMAGES&quot;">
      <data key="d3">9.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Tenant may be awarded Damages if the landlord fails to comply with security deposit regulations, including interest payment deficiencies."</data>
      <data key="d5">"legal rights, compensation"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-bc145ddced779a4e72a5f21656d00d2e</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;TENANT&quot;" target="&quot;COURT OF COMPETENT JURISDICTION&quot;">
      <data key="d3">10.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Tenant can bring a cause of action in the Court of Competent Jurisdiction to challenge the correctness of interest calculations."</data>
      <data key="d5">"legal recourse, dispute resolution"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-bc145ddced779a4e72a5f21656d00d2e</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;TENANT&quot;" target="&quot;FORECLOSURE ACTION&quot;">
      <data key="d3">8.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Tenants must be notified by the Landlord if a Foreclosure Action is filed against the property they occupy, important for their rights."</data>
      <data key="d5">"notification, tenant rights"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-9177bd0c8a93a10bd432b21c5f8d990c</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;TENANT&quot;" target="&quot;SECTION 5-12-090&quot;">
      <data key="d3">8.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Section 5-12-090 outlines remedies available to the Tenant if the Landlord fails to uphold rental agreement standards."</data>
      <data key="d5">"tenant rights, legal action"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-1b28d02fb2d5d40898b1812c5ffa049c</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;TENANT&quot;" target="&quot;TENANT REMEDIES&quot;">
      <data key="d3">9.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Tenant has access to Tenant Remedies, which are legal recourses available when landlords fail to comply with their obligations."</data>
      <data key="d5">"legal rights, tenant protection"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-1b28d02fb2d5d40898b1812c5ffa049c</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;TENANT&quot;" target="&quot;MATERIAL NONCOMPLIANCE&quot;">
      <data key="d3">15.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"If the tenant fails to comply with significant terms of the rental agreement, it can lead to actions taken by the landlord."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Tenant's rights may be violated in cases of Material Noncompliance by the Landlord, impacting their living conditions."</data>
      <data key="d5">"contract breach, compliance issues"&lt;SEP&gt;"tenant rights, compliance"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-bbf2a304267f411fdd75632601e64887&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-49eeebcde41c80ab078e5fdc2db008fa</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;TENANT&quot;" target="&quot;POSSESSION&quot;">
      <data key="d3">10.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Tenant's right to Possession signifies their entitlement to occupy the dwelling unit as per the rental agreement."</data>
      <data key="d5">"occupational rights, tenancy"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-bbf2a304267f411fdd75632601e64887</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;TENANT&quot;" target="&quot;WRITTEN NOTICE&quot;">
      <data key="d3">16.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Tenant may deliver Written Notice to the Landlord to address issues like Material Noncompliance or intent to terminate the rental agreement."&lt;SEP&gt;"The landlord must provide written notice to the tenant regarding breaches, which is a legal requirement in rental agreements."</data>
      <data key="d5">"formal communication, tenant rights"&lt;SEP&gt;"legal process, tenant rights"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-bbf2a304267f411fdd75632601e64887&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-49eeebcde41c80ab078e5fdc2db008fa</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;TENANT&quot;" target="&quot;TENANT'S FAMILY&quot;">
      <data key="d3">7.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Tenant's Family may share rights and responsibilities regarding the occupancy of the Dwelling Unit under the rental agreement."</data>
      <data key="d5">"shared living, tenancy rights"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-bbf2a304267f411fdd75632601e64887</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;TENANT&quot;" target="&quot;FIRE OR CASUALTY DAMAGE&quot;">
      <data key="d3">7.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Tenant's rights and actions are influenced by occurrences of Fire or Casualty Damage as specified in their Rental Agreement."</data>
      <data key="d5">"property damage, tenant rights"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-c3bc1dbbc22da4bbc6a6de45ffaa66df</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;TENANT&quot;" target="&quot;ABANDONMENT&quot;">
      <data key="d3">7.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"When the tenant abandons the dwelling unit, they violate the terms of the rental agreement, permitting the landlord to take action."|&lt;|"violation, legal action"</data>
      <data key="d5">7</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-b6545ef03dc8e11cfc621983d50e00f5</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;TENANT&quot;" target="&quot;COMMUNITY ORGANIZATION&quot;">
      <data key="d3">7.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Tenants may engage with community organizations to seek assistance or advocate for their rights regarding housing issues."."</data>
      <data key="d5">"advocacy, tenant rights"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-8afa5a33f6f01f872089d10f74700726</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;TENANT&quot;" target="&quot;TENANT'S UNION&quot;">
      <data key="d3">7.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Tenants may become members of a tenant's union to collectively advocate for their rights and improve their living conditions."."</data>
      <data key="d5">"advocacy, collective action"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-8afa5a33f6f01f872089d10f74700726</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;TENANT&quot;" target="&quot;STATE OF ILLINOIS&quot;">
      <data key="d3">7.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The laws of the State of Illinois provide additional rights and remedies for tenants beyond those specific to the City of Chicago ordinances."</data>
      <data key="d5">"jurisdiction, legal framework"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-471bca0f3da3db4a8af4c1624c74f5ad</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;TENANT&quot;" target="&quot;CIVIL LEGAL PROCEEDING&quot;">
      <data key="d3">8.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Tenants may engage in civil legal proceedings to enforce their rights as defined in rental agreements and local ordinances."</data>
      <data key="d5">"legal enforcement, rights"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-471bca0f3da3db4a8af4c1624c74f5ad</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;TENANT&quot;" target="&quot;SECURITY DEPOSITS&quot;">
      <data key="d3">9.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Tenants are entitled to returns on their security deposits, and rights regarding these funds are protected under ordinance regulations."</data>
      <data key="d5">"financial rights, tenant advocacy"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-471bca0f3da3db4a8af4c1624c74f5ad</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;TENANT&quot;" target="&quot;CHICAGO NON-EMERGENCY NUMBER 3-1-1&quot;">
      <data key="d3">7.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Tenants can use the Chicago non-emergency number 3-1-1 to inquire about issues related to rental properties and safety regulations."</data>
      <data key="d5">"resources, tenant support"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-471bca0f3da3db4a8af4c1624c74f5ad</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;TENANT&quot;" target="&quot;ORAL AGREEMENT&quot;">
      <data key="d3">8.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"In the case of an oral agreement, tenants are still required to be informed of their rights through documented summaries prepared by landlords."</data>
      <data key="d5">"contractual obligation, rights"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-471bca0f3da3db4a8af4c1624c74f5ad</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;LANDLORD&quot;" target="&quot;OWNER&quot;">
      <data key="d3">8.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The owner of a property is often the landlord, as the landlord's rights directly relate to ownership of the dwelling unit."</data>
      <data key="d5">"ownership, rental rights"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-d2157989b5839c3e9aeb71adca8d9db4</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;LANDLORD&quot;" target="&quot;ILLINOIS&quot;">
      <data key="d3">9.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Landlords in Illinois must comply with state laws regarding the holding of security deposits and their responsibilities."</data>
      <data key="d5">"legal compliance, jurisdiction"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-caa542bbeffaceb300226b5da0f70961</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;LANDLORD&quot;" target="&quot;MUNICIPAL CODE&quot;">
      <data key="d3">9.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The landlord must adhere to the municipal code provisions related to property maintenance and tenant rights."</data>
      <data key="d5">"legal obligations, governance"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-caa542bbeffaceb300226b5da0f70961</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;LANDLORD&quot;" target="&quot;PREMISES&quot;">
      <data key="d3">9.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The landlord is responsible for maintaining and accessing the premises as stipulated in the rental agreement."</data>
      <data key="d5">"property management, landlord responsibilities"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-caa542bbeffaceb300226b5da0f70961</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;LANDLORD&quot;" target="&quot;SECURITY DEPOSITS&quot;">
      <data key="d3">17.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Landlords are responsible for handling security deposits, including adherence to interest regulations and returning deposits to tenants upon termination of agreements."&lt;SEP&gt;"The landlord must hold and manage security deposits according to state laws and ensure they are not commingled with other assets."</data>
      <data key="d5">"financial management, legal compliance"&lt;SEP&gt;"financial obligation, tenant protection"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-471bca0f3da3db4a8af4c1624c74f5ad&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-caa542bbeffaceb300226b5da0f70961</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;LANDLORD&quot;" target="&quot;NOTICE&quot;">
      <data key="d3">9.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The landlord is required to provide notice to the tenant before entering the dwelling unit, ensuring transparency and respect for privacy."</data>
      <data key="d5">"transparency, communication"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-caa542bbeffaceb300226b5da0f70961</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;LANDLORD&quot;" target="&quot;SECURITY DEPOSIT&quot;">
      <data key="d3">37.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Landlord holds the Security Deposit as a guarantee for the Tenant's obligations concerning the rental agreement, to be returned if conditions are met."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Landlord is responsible for managing and returning the Security Deposit according to relevant laws and regulations."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Landlord is responsible for managing security deposits received from the Tenant, including compliance with notification requirements."&lt;SEP&gt;"The landlord collects a security deposit from the tenant as part of the rental agreement to protect against damages and unpaid rent."</data>
      <data key="d5">"financial guarantee, contract"&lt;SEP&gt;"financial obligation, landlord responsibilities"&lt;SEP&gt;"financial obligation, rental agreement"&lt;SEP&gt;"financial responsibility, compliance"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-9177bd0c8a93a10bd432b21c5f8d990c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bbf2a304267f411fdd75632601e64887&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7759df7263a7c6a25e1e83bd43ddc9c9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bc145ddced779a4e72a5f21656d00d2e</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;LANDLORD&quot;" target="&quot;FINANCIAL INSTITUTION&quot;">
      <data key="d3">7.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The landlord deposits the tenant's security deposit in a financial institution as required by law, ensuring its safekeeping."</data>
      <data key="d5">"financial management, legal compliance"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-7759df7263a7c6a25e1e83bd43ddc9c9</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;LANDLORD&quot;" target="&quot;SUCCESSOR LANDLORD&quot;">
      <data key="d3">8.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The successor landlord inherits obligations related to the security deposit from the transferring landlord, ensuring continuity in the rental agreement protection."</data>
      <data key="d5">"property transfer, financial obligation"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-7759df7263a7c6a25e1e83bd43ddc9c9</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;LANDLORD&quot;" target="&quot;THIRTY DAYS&quot;">
      <data key="d3">8.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Landlord must pay interest on the security deposit within Thirty Days to avoid liabilities, indicating strict adherence to regulations."</data>
      <data key="d5">"compliance, financial obligation"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-bc145ddced779a4e72a5f21656d00d2e</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;LANDLORD&quot;" target="&quot;FORTY-FIVE DAYS&quot;">
      <data key="d3">8.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Landlord has a Forty-Five Days window to pay interest on certain prepaid rents, highlighting timelines crucial for legal compliance."</data>
      <data key="d5">"financial timeline, obligation"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-bc145ddced779a4e72a5f21656d00d2e</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;LANDLORD&quot;" target="&quot;FORECLOSURE ACTION&quot;">
      <data key="d3">9.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Landlords are subject to legal actions, specifically Foreclosure Actions, which can terminate or affect rental agreements."</data>
      <data key="d5">"legal consequences, property rights"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-9177bd0c8a93a10bd432b21c5f8d990c</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;LANDLORD&quot;" target="&quot;NOTICE OF CONDITIONS AFFECTING HABITABILITY&quot;">
      <data key="d3">10.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Landlord must provide the Notice of Conditions Affecting Habitability to ensure tenants are informed of any issues that could affect their living conditions."</data>
      <data key="d5">"tenant protection, compliance"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-9177bd0c8a93a10bd432b21c5f8d990c</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;LANDLORD&quot;" target="&quot;SECTION 5-12-070&quot;">
      <data key="d3">26.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Section 5-12-070 establishes the legal responsibilities of the Landlord towards the Tenant in terms of property conditions and services."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Landlord is obligated by Section 5-12-070 to maintain the dwelling unit in a fit and habitable condition, affecting tenant living conditions."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Landlord must comply with Section 5-12-070 as it details regulations affecting the rental agreement and tenant rights."</data>
      <data key="d5">"legal obligation, property maintenance"&lt;SEP&gt;"legal obligations, tenant protection"&lt;SEP&gt;"regulatory compliance, obligations"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-bbf2a304267f411fdd75632601e64887&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c3bc1dbbc22da4bbc6a6de45ffaa66df&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1b28d02fb2d5d40898b1812c5ffa049c</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;LANDLORD&quot;" target="&quot;SECTION 5-12-101&quot;">
      <data key="d3">7.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Landlord must comply with Section 5-12-101 by providing information on bed bug prevention and treatment to tenants."</data>
      <data key="d5">"tenant education, compliance"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-1b28d02fb2d5d40898b1812c5ffa049c</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;LANDLORD&quot;" target="&quot;DEPARTMENT OF HEALTH&quot;">
      <data key="d3">8.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Landlord is required to work alongside the Department of Health to provide necessary educational materials and maintain health standards in properties."</data>
      <data key="d5">"collaboration, health standards"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-1b28d02fb2d5d40898b1812c5ffa049c</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;LANDLORD&quot;" target="&quot;ESSENTIAL SERVICES&quot;">
      <data key="d3">10.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Landlord is obligated to provide Essential Services to ensure the Tenant's health and safety in the dwelling unit."</data>
      <data key="d5">"services obligation, tenant safety"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-bbf2a304267f411fdd75632601e64887</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;LANDLORD&quot;" target="&quot;DAMAGES&quot;">
      <data key="d3">9.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"If the Landlord fails to meet obligations, they may be liable to pay Damages to the Tenant as compensation."</data>
      <data key="d5">"legal liability, compensation"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-bbf2a304267f411fdd75632601e64887</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;LANDLORD&quot;" target="&quot;MATERIAL DEFECTS&quot;">
      <data key="d3">9.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Landlord is responsible for addressing Material Defects in the property to maintain its habitability and comply with the rental agreement."</data>
      <data key="d5">"maintenance obligation, tenant rights"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-bbf2a304267f411fdd75632601e64887</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;LANDLORD&quot;" target="&quot;EMERGENCY REPAIRS&quot;">
      <data key="d3">10.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Landlord is required to conduct Emergency Repairs in a timely manner to ensure the Tenant's safety and health."</data>
      <data key="d5">"urgency, safety"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-bbf2a304267f411fdd75632601e64887</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;LANDLORD&quot;" target="&quot;ILLINOIS CODE OF CIVIL PROCEDURE&quot;">
      <data key="d3">7.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The landlord's actions regarding evictions and rent collections must adhere to the guidelines established by the Illinois Code of Civil Procedure."</data>
      <data key="d5">"legal compliance, eviction process"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-49eeebcde41c80ab078e5fdc2db008fa</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;LANDLORD&quot;" target="&quot;FIRE&quot;">
      <data key="d3">7.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The landlord has the responsibility to address issues related to fire occurrences as they pertain to the rental agreement's termination."</data>
      <data key="d5">"safety concerns, lease termination"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-49eeebcde41c80ab078e5fdc2db008fa</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;LANDLORD&quot;" target="&quot;GOOD FAITH EFFORT&quot;">
      <data key="d3">9.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The landlord must demonstrate a good faith effort to re-rent the unit after the tenant has early terminated the rental agreement."</data>
      <data key="d5">"re-renting, landlord obligations"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-49eeebcde41c80ab078e5fdc2db008fa</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;LANDLORD&quot;" target="&quot;DWELLING UNIT&quot;">
      <data key="d3">10.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The landlord maintains ownership over the dwelling unit and is responsible for its management and repair."|&lt;|"ownership, property management"</data>
      <data key="d5">10</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-b6545ef03dc8e11cfc621983d50e00f5</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;LANDLORD&quot;" target="&quot;INJUNCTIVE RELIEF&quot;">
      <data key="d3">8.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The landlord may seek injunctive relief against the tenant if there are violations of the rental agreement."|&lt;|"legal remedy, violation"</data>
      <data key="d5">8</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-b6545ef03dc8e11cfc621983d50e00f5</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;LANDLORD&quot;" target="&quot;RETALIATORY CONDUCT&quot;">
      <data key="d3">10.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Retaliatory conduct by the landlord against the tenant is prohibited under the laws enforced by the City of Chicago."</data>
      <data key="d5">"prohibition, legal consequences"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-948f888104b901aa818d8a64425e31e7</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;LANDLORD&quot;" target="&quot;COMMUNITY ORGANIZATION&quot;">
      <data key="d3">6.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Community organizations may intervene in disputes involving landlords and tenant rights, often advocating for tenants against unfair practices."."</data>
      <data key="d5">"advocacy, dispute resolution"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-8afa5a33f6f01f872089d10f74700726</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;LANDLORD&quot;" target="&quot;COOK COUNTY&quot;">
      <data key="d3">8.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Landlords must operate within the jurisdiction of Cook County, which has specific regulations and processes for eviction and tenant disputes."."</data>
      <data key="d5">"jurisdiction, legal compliance"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-8afa5a33f6f01f872089d10f74700726</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;LANDLORD&quot;" target="&quot;STATE OF ILLINOIS&quot;">
      <data key="d3">7.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The State of Illinois has regulations applicable to landlords that can affect their responsibilities and obligations in rental agreements."</data>
      <data key="d5">"jurisdiction, legal framework"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-471bca0f3da3db4a8af4c1624c74f5ad</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;LANDLORD&quot;" target="&quot;CIVIL LEGAL PROCEEDING&quot;">
      <data key="d3">8.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Landlords may also enter civil legal proceedings regarding disputes over rental agreements and tenant actions."</data>
      <data key="d5">"legal enforcement, disputes"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-471bca0f3da3db4a8af4c1624c74f5ad</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;LANDLORD&quot;" target="&quot;ORAL AGREEMENT&quot;">
      <data key="d3">8.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Landlords must provide written summaries to tenants even if a rental agreement is established orally, ensuring transparency and compliance with regulations."</data>
      <data key="d5">"regulation compliance, tenant information"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-471bca0f3da3db4a8af4c1624c74f5ad</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;SECURITY DEPOSITS&quot;" target="&quot;COMMISSIONER OF HOUSING&quot;">
      <data key="d3">8.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Commissioner of Housing provides information and updates related to the management of security deposits, including interest rates and obligations to tenants."</data>
      <data key="d5">"financial regulation, tenant rights"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-471bca0f3da3db4a8af4c1624c74f5ad</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;DWELLING UNIT&quot;" target="&quot;SUCCESSOR LANDLORD&quot;">
      <data key="d3">7.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"A successor landlord may take control of a dwelling unit from a previous landlord, maintaining the rental relationship with tenants."</data>
      <data key="d5">"property transfer, landlord responsibilities"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-d2157989b5839c3e9aeb71adca8d9db4</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;SUCCESSOR LANDLORD&quot;" target="&quot;NOTICE OF TRANSFER&quot;">
      <data key="d3">9.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The successor landlord is obligated to provide the tenant with a notice of transfer when they take over the property, as required by law."</data>
      <data key="d5">"legal requirement, landlord obligation"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-7759df7263a7c6a25e1e83bd43ddc9c9</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;SUCCESSOR LANDLORD&quot;" target="&quot;TRANSFEROR&quot;">
      <data key="d3">9.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Successor Landlord assumes responsibilities from the Transferor, including managing the security deposit effectively."</data>
      <data key="d5">"transfer of responsibility, landlord transition"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-bc145ddced779a4e72a5f21656d00d2e</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;ACCESS&quot;" target="&quot;EMERGENCY&quot;">
      <data key="d3">10.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"In emergencies, the landlord can access the unit without notice, prioritizing safety and urgent repairs."</data>
      <data key="d5">"emergency procedure, immediate access"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-caa542bbeffaceb300226b5da0f70961</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;CITY COMPTROLLER&quot;" target="&quot;INTEREST RATE&quot;">
      <data key="d3">9.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The City Comptroller calculates and announces the Interest Rate for security deposits based on the prevailing rates in local banks."</data>
      <data key="d5">"financial governance, rate determination"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-bc145ddced779a4e72a5f21656d00d2e</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;CITY COMPTROLLER&quot;" target="&quot;MAYOR&quot;">
      <data key="d3">7.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Mayor directs the City Comptroller in preparing and publishing information related to security deposits and tenant rights."</data>
      <data key="d5">"administrative oversight, public communication"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-bc145ddced779a4e72a5f21656d00d2e</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;CITY COMPTROLLER&quot;" target="&quot;PAMPHLET OR BROCHURE&quot;">
      <data key="d3">7.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The City Comptroller oversees the production and distribution of pamphlets or brochures detailing tenant and landlord rights regarding security deposits."</data>
      <data key="d5">"public information, tenant awareness"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-bc145ddced779a4e72a5f21656d00d2e</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;PUBLIC SERVICE ANNOUNCEMENTS&quot;" target="&quot;COMMISSIONER OF HOUSING&quot;">
      <data key="d3">9.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Commissioner of Housing is responsible for preparing and distributing public service announcements that inform tenants about important housing regulations and rates."</data>
      <data key="d5">"information dissemination, regulation"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-471bca0f3da3db4a8af4c1624c74f5ad</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;SECTION 5-12-070&quot;" target="&quot;MATERIAL NONCOMPLIANCE&quot;">
      <data key="d3">8.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Material Noncompliance identified in Section 5-12-070 highlights specific landlord obligations and the consequences of failing to meet them."</data>
      <data key="d5">"legal compliance, housing standards"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-1b28d02fb2d5d40898b1812c5ffa049c</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;BED BUGS&quot;" target="&quot;INFORMATIONAL BROCHURE&quot;">
      <data key="d3">7.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Informational Brochure provides information specifically about handling Bed Bugs, aligning with the legal requirements set forth in rental agreements."</data>
      <data key="d5">"education, pest control"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-1b28d02fb2d5d40898b1812c5ffa049c</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;BUILDING CODE&quot;" target="&quot;LAW&quot;">
      <data key="d3">9.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The laws of Illinois include building codes that landlords are required to follow to ensure safe living conditions for tenants."."</data>
      <data key="d5">"legal obligation, safety"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-8afa5a33f6f01f872089d10f74700726</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;GOOD FAITH EFFORT&quot;" target="&quot;FAIR RENTAL&quot;">
      <data key="d3">8.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Determining a fair rental is critical for the landlord to satisfy legal obligations in re-renting a unit under good faith efforts."</data>
      <data key="d5">"market value, rental terms"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-49eeebcde41c80ab078e5fdc2db008fa</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;LAW&quot;" target="&quot;RETALIATORY ACTION&quot;">
      <data key="d3">10.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The law specifically prohibits retaliatory actions by landlords against tenants, establishing protections for tenants."."</data>
      <data key="d5">"legal protection, retaliation"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-8afa5a33f6f01f872089d10f74700726</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;LAW&quot;" target="&quot;TENANT CONDUCT&quot;">
      <data key="d3">10.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Tenant conduct that is protected by law serves as a defense in legal matters involving alleged retaliatory actions by landlords."."</data>
      <data key="d5">"legal protection, tenant rights"</data>
      <data key="d6">chunk-8afa5a33f6f01f872089d10f74700726</data>
    </edge>
  </graph>
